documentType: evidence inventory and chain of custody form
summary: This document is an FBI evidence inventory and chain of custody log for items seized from a location in Palm Beach, Florida. It lists numerous items including massage tables, framed photos (including a nude photo), personal items, and media, and tracks the custody transfers of this evidence from 2006 to at least 2020.

events.title: Evidence Collection in Palm Beach
events.description: Items were collected from Palm Beach, FL, 33480, and entered into evidence under case 31E-MM-108062. The inventory includes massage tables, photos, personal items, and media.

events.title: Last Inventory of Evidence
events.description: The evidence items were last inventoried, indicating the materials were still in custody over 14 years after seizure.

keyFacts: Evidence seized includes two massage tables (one beige, one brown), multiple framed photos, and a 'black framed photo of nude girl'.
Personal and sensitive items were collected, including vibrators, a bottle of 'Joy Jelly', a high school transcript, VHS tapes, CDs, and shredded paper.
The evidence was collected on August 28, 2006, from Palm Beach, Florida, under FBI case number 31E-MM-108062.
The chain of custody log shows the evidence was transferred multiple times, including to New York, and was last inventoried on August 4, 2020.
The document is an official FBI FD-192 form and FD-1087, detailing the acquisition and custody history of physical evidence.
